    {
      "note_no": "5190",
      "note": "Ikram: two ideas are prominent in the word. (1) the idea of generosity, as proceeding from the person whose attribute it is, and (2) the idea of honour, as given by others to the person whose attribute it is. Both these ideas are summed up in \"nobility\". To make the meaning quite clear, I have employed in the translation the two words \"Bounty and Honour\" for the single word Ikram. The same attributes recur in the last verse of this Surah. In the Fact of Allah's Eternity is the Hope of our Future."
