      "note": "Lit., \"face\", or \"countenance\", a term used metonymically in classical Arabic to denote the \"self or \"whole being\" of a person - in this case, the essential Being, or Reality, of God. Cf. also 28:88, \"Everything isbound to perish, save His [eternal] Self."
